article.headline: Coppin St. 50, Howard 46
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Tywain McKee's 19 points and Coppin State's stifling defense helped the Eagles to a 50-46 win over Howard on Saturday. Antwan Harrison added nine points, and the Eagles (9-18, 7-8 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) got 16 points from their bench. Darek Mitchell led the Bison (9-18, 5-10 MEAC) with 14 points, and Kandi Mukole scored 10. The Bison shot just 31 percent, compiling the lowest shooting percentage and point total by a Coppin State opponent this season. The Eagles used an 8-1 run midway through the second half to take control of a tight game, building a 40-30 lead with 9:03 remaining. But Howard rallied with a 13-5 run to get within two in the final minute. Darryl Roberts hit a jumper with 29 seconds remaining and the shot clock winding town to give Coppin State a 47-43 advantage, and McKee sealed the win when he hit a pair of free throws with eight seconds left.
